
[PTOGGLE]


  Ptoggle is similar to the guild function 'toggle' which allows you
  to enable or disable various settings that are relavent to your
  current polymorph. This command is only relevant to polymorph forms
  that support it.

  Note that settings do NOT save automatically.


Usage:  ptoggle <argument>


Examples:


  For the polymorph treehouse form, a function can be enabled or
  disabled by 'ptoggle listen'.

Typing 'ptoggle' displays all current toggle settings.


